1
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:07,610
Many strange tales
are told of this jungle.

2
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:09,650
But none so strange...

3
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:13,080
As the tale of the cub we call Mowgli.

4
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,890
You must be the very
worst wolf I've ever seen.

5
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:31,320
Yeah, but if that branch didn't break,
I would've made it.

6
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,330
Crossing upwind,
breaking from your numbers.

7
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,880
If you can't learn to run with the pack...

8
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,490
One of these days,
you'll be someone's dinner.

9
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:38,850
- How'd we do?
- Not Mowgli, again.

10
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,530
- He's never gonna make the council.
- Let's go!

11
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:43,400
Race you to the top!

12
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,760
It was higher ground.

13
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:48,080
Wolves don't hide in trees.

14
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,400
I can't keep up with them, Bagheera.

15
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,600
I tried. I just picked the wrong tree.

16
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,090
It was a dead tree.

17
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,610
How was I supposed to know
it was dead?

18
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,890
It had a fig vine.

19
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:00,970
Any tree girdled by a creeper
is either dead or close to it.

20
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:04,170
- These are things a wolf must know.
- Yeah.

21
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:07,400
But if the branch didn't break,
Iwould've made it.

22
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,240
I realise you weren't born a wolf...

23
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,290
But couldn't you at least act like one?

24
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,930
Bagheera'. When I found him...

25
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,650
Many years ago...

26
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:23,640
He was just an infant,
abandoned in the woods.

27
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,290
Get the deer!

28
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,600
If he
was going to survive...

29
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,290
I knew he needed a people.

30
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,240
A people to protect him.

31
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:37,200
That's why I entrusted him
to the wolves.

32
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,280
Look well, wolves.

33
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:47,010
Akela was
a just and noble leader.

34
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:50,530
He allowed Mowgli to dwell
among them, all those years.

35
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:56,640
The trouble was, wolves grew so fast...

36
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,370
And Mowgli...

37
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:01,170
Let's just say he liked to take his time.

38
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,480
Mowgli, pick me up high!

39
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:05,200
- My turn!
- Stop. Not now.

40
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,520
It was Raksha
who raised him.

41
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,720
She was the only mother he ever knew.

42
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,770
- Come on, let's play!
- I don't feel like playing, Gray.

43
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,970
Come on, you're my brother.
You have to play with me.

44
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,010
Let's go chase some mice.

45
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,970
How did it go?

46
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:23,130
Caught me again.

47
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,810
If it's meant to be...

48
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,880
It will be.

49
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,210
Let me hear the law.

50
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,600
"This is the law of the jungle...

51
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,330
"As old and as true as the sky.

52
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,920
"The wolf that keeps it will prosper...

53
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,850
"But the wolf that breaks it will die.

54
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,530
"Like the creeper that girdles
the tree trunk...

55
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:46,040
"The law runneth over and back.

56
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,770
"For the strength of the pack
is the wolf...

57
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:52,370
"And the strength of the wolf
is the pack."

58
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,920
Soon,
the rain ceased to fall

59
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,890
and the dry season arrived.

60
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,290
Heat crept through the jungle...

61
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,850
Turning it yellow...

62
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,240
Then brown...

63
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,810
Then black.

64
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,690
But that year...

65
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,840
Was the driest season
that anyone could remember.

66
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,160
Even the mohwa didn't flower.

67
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,090
My leaf.

68
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,640
This is mine. Mine, mine, mine.

69
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:59,250
There's a rock. That's mud. That's mud.

70
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,890
There's a rock. That's my rock.

71
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,690
That's my rock.
Nobody touches my rock.

72
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,280
There's another rock.
Two rocks. Three rocks.

73
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,280
Peace rock? Peace rock!

74
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,920
It's the truce! The water truce!

75
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,130
It's the water truce!

76
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:17,080
It had been
many, many years

77
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:19,160
since the peace rock was revealed...

78
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,160
And the water truce was called.

79
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,720
Hunting at the riverbank

80
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,800
- was now forbidden...

81
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:35,650
Because, by law of the jungle,
drinking comes before eating.

82
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:38,880
So, you could come to the peace rock,
on a day like this...

83
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:42,160
And find all people side-by-side.

84
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,800
Don't forget.

85
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,930
No hunting.

86
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Playing only-

87
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,610
playing, only. I got it, ami.

88
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,080
And remember...

89
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,810
Not everyone here has seen
a man-cub in the jungle before.

90
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,370
So, behave yourself.

91
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,400
Okay, can I go now?

92
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,770
Take the pups with you.

93
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,890
Wait for me!

94
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:11,600
Come on, Gray!

95
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:13,960
Oh, take a look at this guy.

96
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:15,920
Excuse me.

97
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,760
Sorry.

98
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,090
- He's walking on two legs.
- Don't stare.

99
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,480
Hey, look. A wild boar.

100
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:24,040
- And a rhino.
- And a mongoose.

101
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,200
Everybody's here.

102
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,640
Is that a peacock?

103
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,890
- Ooh, a stick!
- Oh, that's my stick.

104
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,490
- I like this stick.
- Seriously, that's my stick.

105
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,730
- This is my stick.
- No, that's my stick!

106
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,370
- Let go of my stick!
- It's a water truce!

107
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,730
It's a water truce!

108
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,890
Sorry.

109
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,480
My bad! It's involuntary.

110
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,610
I could pee on it.

111
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,290
Watch yourself, please.

112
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,080
Dad, what is that?

113
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,890
I think that's a man-cub.

114
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:50,040
What's a man-cub doing here?

115
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,240
Whoa. Don't forget the truce.

116
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,050
I know the law, bucks.

117
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,450
What is that?

118
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,930
- Weird.
- That's weird.

119
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,440
Akelai Mowgli.

120
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:27,450
What was the rule about your tricks?

121
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,600
It's not the wolf way.

122
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,440
No more tricks.

123
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:36,290
Chin up, little one.

124
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,010
We'll make you a fine wolf, yet.

125
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,120
What about me?
Am I gonna be a fine wolf?

126
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,410
Look at me howl!

127
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,720
In some packs, the runt gets eaten.

128
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,120
Oh...

129
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,130
Mowgli, behind me.

130
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:12,560
Don't leave my side.

131
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:02,240
Everyone comes to peace rock.
So many smells to catch up on.

132
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,610
But, um...

133
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,530
I can't help but notice...

134
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:18,200
There's this strange odour today.

135
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,730
What is it, this scent that I'm on?

136
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,280
I almost...

137
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,560
I almost think it was some kind of...

138
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,440
Man-cub.

139
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:38,090
Mowgli belongs
to my pack, Shere Khan.

140
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,560
Mowgli?

141
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,320
They've given it a name.

142
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:47,880
When was it we came to adopt
man into the jungle?

143
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,890
He's just a cub.

144
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:54,370
Does my face not remind you
of what a grown man can do?

145
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,410
Shift your hunting ground
for a few years...

146
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:02,450
And everyone forgets
how the law works.

147
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:04,690
Well, let me remind you.

148
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,440
A man-cub becomes man...

149
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,440
And man is forbidden!

150
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,610
- What do you know about law?
- Raksha.

151
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:17,210
Hunting for pleasure. Killing for power.

152
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,920
You've never known law.
The cub is mine!

153
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:21,640
Mine to me.

154
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,890
So, go back to where you came from,
you burned beast!

155
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:30,760
The tiger knows who rules
this part of the jungle.

156
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,770
I'm sure he doesn't mean to come here
and make threats.

157
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,490
Especially during a water truce.

158
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:49,970
No, I'm deeply respectful of these laws
that keep us safe.

159
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,530
So, here's my promise.

160
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,170
Nothing lasts forever.

161
00:11:56,280 --> 00:12:00,290
The rains will return
and the river will rise.

162
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:04,160
And when this rock disappears,
that truce will end.

163
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:08,170
You want to protect him, fine.

164
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:14,200
But ask yourselves,
how many lives is a man-cub worth?

165
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,530
Bagheera". How many lives?

166
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,840
Who could answer that question?

167
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,210
- The rain!
- Rain!

168
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,360
- Rain!
- The rain!

169
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,410
Keep it dry, keep it dry, keep it dry.

170
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:14,330
These quills
get stuck on everything!

171
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:18,880
Bagheera". When the rains returned...

172
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:22,400
It was a question
the council had to face.

173
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:50,770
They deliberated and they argued...

174
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,600
For many days.

175
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:59,880
What do you think they're talking about?

176
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:04,760
No one had ever
come between the pack before.

177
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:08,440
But Shere Khan's threat...

178
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,600
Was not to be ignored.

179
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:21,410
Mowgli, you're not supposed
to go up there!

180
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,290
He's got to go.

181
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Look at the skies.

182
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,280
Shere Khan may be heading here
as we speak.

183
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,040
Please!

184
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,570
I'm leaving.

185
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,370
I don't want to see anyone get hurt.

186
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,520
Mowgli, go back to the den!

187
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,330
A man-cub belongs with man.

188
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,290
We raised him as one of our own!

189
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,130
- He'll have the boy, either way.
- Akela.

190
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,970
Maybe I can be of help.

191
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,490
The boy's right.

192
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:03,530
Maybe it's time he found another people.

193
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,370
- No.
-I'm the one who brought him to you.

194
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,650
And now I'll return him
to where he belongs.

195
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,130
I won't let you.

196
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:11,680
He's my cub!

197
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,160
We knew this day would come.

198
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,610
We are the only family he's ever known!

199
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:16,840
Raksha.

200
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:21,210
It's the only place he'll be safe.

201
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,130
It's okay, ami.

202
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,850
I won't go far.

203
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:31,680
I'll come back and visit.

204
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,440
Never forget this...

205
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,200
You're mine.

206
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:39,890
Mine to me.

207
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:44,160
No matter where you go,
or what they may call you...

208
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,730
You will always be...

209
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,440
My son.

210
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,890
I wish I could tell you...

211
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,570
That the wolves
could've fought Shere Khan.

212
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,560
But this is not that kind of a tale.

213
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,770
The turtles like me.

214
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,760
Maybe the crocodiles.

215
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,370
What about the rhinos?

216
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,400
They always let me hang around.

217
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,730
Of course, the rhinos sleep standing up.

218
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,250
I don't think I'd be very good at that.

219
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,730
It's either the turtles or the crocodiles.

220
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,610
Which one do you think is better?

221
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,000
Bagheerai neither.

222
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,850
What do you mean?

223
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,240
I'm bringing you to the man village.

224
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,600
What?

225
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:05,570
Bagheera, I don't know man.

226
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,850
You will.

227
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,450
You always said
we're not supposed

228
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,610
to go near a man village.

229
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,610
That was different.

230
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,370
Why is it different?

231
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,400
You always said, "stay away
from the man village...

232
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,090
"Because you might fall in a trap...

233
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,770
"Or get eaten,
or get hurt by flying rocks."

234
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,600
I know what I said.

235
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,720
Whoa. Elephants.

236
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:35,320
- Bow your head.
- Why?

237
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:37,480
Show them respect.

238
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:40,440
The elephants
created this jungle.

239
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,650
Where they made furrows
with their tusks,

240
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,010
the rivers ran.

241
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,890
Where they blew with
their trunks, the leaves fell.

242
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,320
They made all that belongs.

243
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,480
The mountains, the trees...

244
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,800
The birds in the trees.

245
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,490
But they did not make you.

246
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,250
That is why you must go.

247
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,050
What if I live with the nilgai?

248
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:28,120
No.

249
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,810
Or the mongoose?

250
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,530
This is not a discussion.

251
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,010
But this is my home!

252
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:34,530
I don't even know what man's like.

253
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,970
You'll learn.

254
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,360
But I wanna stay in the jungle.

255
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:39,090
Why do I have to go there?

256
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,400
Because the jungle
is no longer safe for you.

257
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,610
You're being hunted...

258
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,050
B'! 8 “get.

259
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:46,090
Only man can protect you now.

260
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,160
Whoa!

261
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:51,210
This isn't fair.
You're not giving me a choice.

262
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,970
There's a lot of stuff
you're not telling me, too.

263
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:54,650
Don't think I didn't notice.

264
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,530
You say you're taking me
where I came from...

265
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,130
But you found me in the jungle.

266
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,690
Are you bringing me back
to the jungle? No.

267
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:02,250
Why are you bringing me
to the man village

268
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,640
if you found me in the jungle?

269
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,720
And why does the tiger
hate me so much?

270
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,800
Does he know me?
Sure seems like he knows me.

271
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,970
Down.

272
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,810
What? Now we have to bow
to the buffalo, too?

273
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,890
Listen to me. This is not a game.

274
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,930
You're gonna run to that ravine.

275
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,930
What are you talking about?

276
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:20,850
Go to the north,
where the sky glows at night.

277
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,000
I'll find you on that path.

278
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,370
Bagheera, I'm not taking one
more step until you tell me...

279
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,130
Bagheerai run, Mowgli!

280
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:55,960
Run!

281
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,250
Gray, what's wrong?

282
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,370
Why don't you come outside and play?

283
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,120
What is that?

284
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,090
Why did he have to leave?

285
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,290
Gray.

286
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:47,330
We could've protected him.
We shouldn't have let him go.

287
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,250
I miss him, too.

288
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:52,370
What's important is, he's safe now.

289
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,770
Get inside.

290
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:49,970
I suppose you know why I've come.

291
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,930
The man-cub has left the jungle.

292
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,200
I thought I made myself clear.

293
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,560
I wanted him turned over to me.

294
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,480
We no longer harbour him.

295
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,320
He has left the pack.

296
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:13,010
And where, may I ask, has he gone?

297
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:19,520
He's with his own kind now.

298
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,090
So, the man-cub has left the jungle.

299
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,170
Akelai that's right.

300
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,930
You and I no longer have a quarrel.

301
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:31,000
And, most importantly...

302
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,490
We have peace.

303
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:41,080
I guess it's done, then.

304
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,410
Unless I can draw him...

305
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,890
Back out!

306
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,850
Akela!

307
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:53,050
Have I got your attention now?

308
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:56,000
I didn't want it to be this way.

309
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:58,360
I made it so simple.

310
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:02,160
All I asked for was one thing,
and you denied me!

311
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,160
That ends now.

312
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:07,210
Spread the word.

313
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:11,130
Until I have the man-cub,
these hills are my hills.

314
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:13,730
You did not respond to reason!

315
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,930
So now, you will know fear.

316
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,370
Bagheera?

317
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,000
Hmm?

318
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:53,250
Hey, there.

319
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:58,370
Do you have a language?

320
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,370
You're kind of cute, I guess.

321
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,530
You want a bite?

322
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,440
Come on.

323
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:13,170
Come here. Come on, it's all right.

324
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:14,650
Don't be afraid.

325
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,690
Come on.

326
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,370
Hey, those are mine!

327
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:34,410
Hey, come back!

328
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,200
Those are mine!

329
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:41,490
Drop it!

330
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,410
Hello?

331
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:18,450
Who's out there?

332
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:20,730
Kaai hi, little cub.

333
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,800
Oh, no. Don't be scared.

334
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:26,770
I'm not gonna hurt you.

335
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:32,930
I was just passing through.
I don't want any trouble.

336
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:35,080
There's no trouble.

337
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,970
Are you alone out here?

338
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:40,600
Mmm. That's not good.

339
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,440
We should never be alone.

340
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,440
I'm waiting for a friend.

341
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:48,440
He should be here soon.

342
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,970
I can stay with you,
until he gets here.

343
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:55,290
Would that be all right?

344
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,440
I'll keep you safe.

345
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:04,450
Just you and me, sweet thing.

346
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:09,090
Who are you?

347
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:14,050
Kaa.

348
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:22,240
Poor, sweet little cub.

349
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:26,200
What are you doing
so deep in the jungle?

350
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:29,320
This is my home.

351
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,530
Don't you know what you are?

352
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:35,960
I know what you are.

353
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:40,850
I know where you came from.

354
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,450
You do?

355
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,490
Yes.

356
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,490
Would you like to see?

357
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,010
Yeah.

358
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,530
Kaa". Mostly, men stay in their village...

359
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:07,200
Far from the dark of the jungle.

360
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,050
But sometimes...

361
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,730
They travel.

362
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:12,850
And when they do...

363
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,000
Their caves breathe in the dark.

364
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,690
They call it...

365
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:21,530
The red flower.

366
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,400
Man's creation.

367
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,530
It brings warmth and light...

368
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:39,050
And destruction to all that it touches.

369
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:44,730
Who is that?

370
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:47,960
The traveller, protecting his cub.

371
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:13,840
Shere Khan ended
the man's life that night.

372
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:20,250
But not before he was burned
by the red flower's touch.

373
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:25,080
He ran so fast, he didn't
notice the cub he left behind.

374
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:37,160
And that cub...

375
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:38,450
Was you.

376
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:05,130
The panther found you.

377
00:34:16,680 --> 00:34:19,810
Oh, you poor, sweet thing.

378
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:24,280
You want to stay in the jungle?

379
00:34:29,160 --> 00:34:31,480
You can be with me, if you want.

380
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,650
I'll keep you close.

381
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:38,490
Let go of your fear, now.

382
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:43,560
Trust...

383
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,170
In me.

384
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:15,720
Relax, kid.

385
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,210
No need to get worked up. Okay?

386
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:19,330
- Where am I?
- Uh...

387
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,520
This is a cave. It's my cave.

388
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:26,170
You don't remember
what happened, do you?

389
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:28,560
- No.
- I saved your life.

390
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,610
Yeah, I snatched you
from the jaws of death.

391
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,920
The coils of death, if you will.

392
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,970
And lucky for you...

393
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,240
Your new favourite hero,
old Baloo, here...

394
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:40,720
Just happened to be passing by.

395
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:41,880
Uh, no big deal.

396
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:44,210
Just tell me this.

397
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:45,930
Can you...

398
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:48,570
Climb?

399
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:51,480
Yeah.

400
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:54,730
Then let's quit wasting time
and get on with it.

401
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:56,410
Get on with what?

402
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,920
Payback, kid. Payback.

403
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:02,050
What do you mean "payback"?
Payback for what?

404
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,240
You owe me, kid.

405
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,130
You owe me. You owe me.

406
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,280
Slow down.

407
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,210
- And you're gonna pay back.
- But, but...

408
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,490
Because that's right.

409
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,810
You're gonna do the right thing.

410
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:13,960
That's the right thing to do.

411
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:15,490
You're gonna pay me back,
because you owe me.

412
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:16,720
You got it?

413
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,450
Okay, here's our little task.

414
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:29,600
You see that golden stuff,
dripping down there?

415
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,410
That's called "honey."

416
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:33,440
All you need to do, little one...

417
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,090
For payback purposes...

418
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:37,610
Is to just shimmy on up there...

419
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:40,330
And get me that thing up there
that's making that funny noise...

420
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:42,010
And bring it back down.

421
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:45,880
You're kidding me, right?

422
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,400
No, not really.

423
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:51,090
I can get killed
going up there.

424
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,480
Kid!

425
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:55,090
Kid, kid, kid. Try to understand this.

426
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:56,760
I'm a bear.

427
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,490
It means that I have to eat my weight...

428
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:00,690
Every day...

429
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,490
For hibernation purposes.

430
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,210
I know I'm asking for a lot...

431
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,410
But I don't climb and you do.

432
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:11,120
Look, I really need your help.
Winter's coming.

433
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,280
You don't want me to go to sleep...

434
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:15,280
And never wake up.

435
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:42,080
There are a lot of bees up here.

436
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:43,930
Yeah, some.

437
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:46,370
But don't worry. These ones don't sting.

438
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,120
Attaboy!

439
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:57,410
Ow! I'm getting stung!

440
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:01,720
Okay-

441
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:05,650
I would've done this myself,
but I'm afraid of heights.

442
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:07,290
Oh, boy. Here we go again.

443
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,760
Why don't you mind your own business?

444
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:10,080
You can do it!

445
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:12,250
- He's just gonna run away.
- Not this one.

446
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:14,170
As soon as the monkeys get
stung, they always run away.

447
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,410
- He's not a monkey. A man-cub.
- What is he?

448
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:18,690
A man-cub?
Yeah! Could you keep your voice down?

449
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,040
I'm trying to concentrate.

450
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:23,360
- Everything going a-okay up there?
- Ow!

451
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,920
Oh, boy. Looks like you got another one.

452
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:27,440
- Buzz off.
-It's a man-cub.

453
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,970
- A man-cub?
- Yeah, it's a man-cub.

454
00:39:29,120 --> 00:39:31,410
- It's not a monkey?
- No, it's a man-cub!

455
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:34,450
You have never been
a more endangered species...

456
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,130
Than you are at this moment.

457
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:38,530
You're doing an amazing job!

458
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:40,130
I'm getting stung!

459
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:41,930
Oh, boy. Here we go again.

460
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:43,810
-It's not a monkey, Fred.
-It's a man-cub.

461
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,330
- A man-cub?
- Yeah, it's a man-cub.

462
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,050
- Can you believe it?
- Are you sure?

463
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:48,770
Would you please shut up?

464
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:50,330
He)', up there!

465
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:52,640
Everything is
going fantastically, I see.

466
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:55,800
Ow!

467
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,890
You got it!
Believe in yourself!

468
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,280
-There you go!
- Ow!

469
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:07,970
Come on! Almost!

470
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:09,840
Yeah!

471
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:11,320
Yeah!

472
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:14,840
Oh. Yeah!

473
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:16,690
Uh-oh.

474
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:21,810
Fred?

475
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:36,000
Oh, yeah, exfoliate me.

476
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:41,280
You said they didn't sting.

477
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,330
What do you call this?

478
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,440
How the heck did you do that?

479
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,680
Oh, those must have been females!

480
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:50,810
They look like males
from down here.

481
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,730
Females do sting.

482
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,770
Just put some honey on those.

483
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:57,210
- Honey? Really?
- Yeah.

484
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,450
You put it on, you lick it off.
You feel much better.

485
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,690
It's nature's ointment.

486
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:03,370
I put it everywhere.

487
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:08,160
Thanks.

488
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:09,570
Okay, so, we're even now!

489
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,170
Hold on a minute.

490
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:12,800
What's your name anyway?

491
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:14,800
We were never properly introduced.

492
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,880
- Mowgli.
- Mowgli?

493
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:20,520
Mowgli is a terrific name.

494
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:23,250
I bet you got that one
all to yourself, too.

495
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:24,880
Hey!

496
00:41:25,080 --> 00:41:26,410
Mowgli, look...

497
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:29,090
I got a lot of gathering to do
these next couple of weeks...

498
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:31,650
On account of the hibernation.

499
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,600
I could really use your help.

500
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:35,090
You know, if you stuck around...

501
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:37,640
I can't. I have to go to the man village.

502
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,480
Uh...

503
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,130
For what reason, man village?

504
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:43,440
I don't have a choice.
There's a tiger hunting me.

505
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:45,240
Really? Why a tiger?

506
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:46,930
Because I'm a man-cub, all right?

507
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,450
Just leave me alone.

508
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:54,450
Hey! Mowgli, my friend,
my buddy, my pal.

509
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:56,130
Slow down a second, handsome.

510
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:58,480
Bagheera said I have to go
to the man village.

511
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:02,770
Oh, Bagheera! I know him. Sure.

512
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,520
You know what his problem is?

513
00:42:04,680 --> 00:42:06,840
He always plays by the rules.

514
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:09,010
And, sometimes rules
were meant to be...

515
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,480
Well, not necessarily broken,
but certainly bent.

516
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:14,040
And definitely reinterpreted.
Don't you think?

517
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:16,810
He told me to go to the man village,
so, that's where I'm gonna go!

518
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:17,930
Okay, fine.

519
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,650
You wanna go to the man village,
have it your way.

520
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:21,640
In fact, I'll do you one better.

521
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,690
I'll take you there myself.

522
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:25,680
Come on, let's go. It's getting late.

523
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:33,090
Bare necessities

524
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:34,160
forget about

525
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:38,200
your worries and your strife

526
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:41,840
I mean the bare necessities

527
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,370
what's that?

528
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:45,810
That's a song about the good life.

529
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:48,090
What's a song?

530
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:50,930
You never
heard a song before?

531
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:52,970
Everyone's got a song.

532
00:42:53,120 --> 00:42:54,720
Didn't the wolves ever sing?

533
00:42:54,920 --> 00:42:56,130
I don't know.

534
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,610
Uh... oh...

535
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,330
We recited the law of the jungle.

536
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:03,010
"This is the law of the jungle...

